1. X3D specification data (Web3D Consortium) — BUNDLED
===============================================================================

The X3D Unified Object Model (X3DUOM) XML files used to drive code generation
and conformance tests:

    src/x3d_cpp_gen/data/X3dUnifiedObjectModel-4.0.xml
    tests/fixtures/X3dUnifiedObjectModel-4.1.xml
    tests/fixtures/uom/X3dUnifiedObjectModel-3.0.xml .. 3.3.xml

are artifacts of the X3D Architecture International Standard (ISO/IEC 19775),
published by the Web3D Consortium at https://www.web3d.org/specifications/ and
made available royalty-free for any use. They are redistributed here under the
Web3D Consortium open-source (BSD-style) license:
https://www.web3d.org/x3d/content/examples/Basic/license.html

    Copyright (c) the X3D / Web3D Consortium contributors. Redistribution and
    use in source and binary forms, with or without modification, are permitted
    provided that the copyright notice and conditions are retained and that the
    names of the Web3D Consortium and its contributors are not used to endorse
