NOT bundled (size + per-file attribution): the X3D conformance example archive
and the X3DJSAIL canonical reference fixtures derived from it. Point a local
checkout at the X3D_CORPUS_DIR environment variable to run the corpus / gate
suites; without it those tests skip cleanly.

NOT bundled (fetched on demand by examples/cpu_raster/assets/kelp_flythrough/
fetch_kelp.sh into a git-ignored exhibit/ dir): the "Kelp Forest Exhibit" X3D
scene by Don Brutzman, Naval Postgraduate School (NPS) MOVES Institute
(http://faculty.nps.edu/brutzman/kelp). Free use with credit to NPS MOVES per
the scene's accessRights metadata. Used only by the optional kelp-flythrough
example; no part of it is committed here.

